What a fabulous night!

We were thrilled to kick off Flux's 2025 with a new play from longtime Flux collaborator, Montserrat Mendez. On Monday, February 3, at 6:30pm ET we hosted a staged reading of <em>Rebecca Roman Redd at the Most Dangerous Hour</em>, directed by Christine Zagrobelny, at Playwrights Downtown's Studio 3F, 440 Lafayette, NYC.

[gallery size="medium" link="file" columns="2" ids="11546,11547,11548,11549,11550,11551,11552,11553,11554,11555,11556,11557"]
<h2 style="text-align: center;"></h2>
The cast of <em>Rebecca Roman Redd at the Most Dangerous Hour </em>featured an exciting mix of Flux Creative Partners and newer collaborators, including: Tonia E. Anderson, Aaron Parker Fouhey, Christopher Moncayo-Torres, Chester Poon, Corinna Schulenburg, Alisha Spielmann, and Isaiah Tanenbaum. Jason Tseng was the lead organizer and dramaturg, and Jodi Witherell was the stage manager.

<b><i>Rebecca Roman Redd at the Most Dangerous Hour</i></b><i>,</i> by Montserrat Mendez, is a sexy, farcical comedy about a delightfully disconnected, mega-successful author navigating her identity and past loves when her wildly popular YA series about a werewolf hunter suddenly becomes all too real. The play was developed over 2024 through <a href="https://www.fluxtheatre.org/core-work/">Flux's Core Work program.</a>

